s. This category of loans declined by $47 million during 2012.", "bbox": [162.5, 775.6, 990.8, 796.5]}, {"text": "Since December 31, 2012, our nonowner-occupied CRE portfolio has increased by approximately $287 million,", "bbox": [162.5, 818.7, 1097.4, 839.5]}, {"text": "or 5.1%, as many of our clients have taken advantage of opportunities to permanently refinance their loans at", "bbox": [162.5, 843.7, 1073.2, 864.5]}, {"text": "historically low interest rates.", "bbox": [162.5, 868.7, 409.5, 889.5]}, {"text": "If the economic recovery stalls, it may weaken the CRE market fundamentals (i.e., vacancy rates, the stability of", "bbox": [162.5, 911.7, 1101.6, 932.5]}, {"text": "rental income and asset values), leading to reduced cash flow to support debt service payments. Reduced client", "bbox": [162.5, 936.7, 1088.6, 957.5]}, {"text": "cash flow would adversely affect our ability to collect such payments. Accordingly, the value of CRE loan", "bbox": [162.5, 961.7, 1051.4, 982.5]}, {"text": "portfolio could be adversely affected.", "bbox": [162.5, 986.7, 474.8, 1007.5]}, {"text": "Commercial lease financing.", "bbox": [162.5, 1029.5, 409.9, 1050.3]}, {"text": "We conduct commercial lease financing arrangements through our Key", "bbox": [430.8, 1029.7, 1026.7, 1050.5]}, {"text": "Equipment Finance line of business and have both the scale and array of products to compete in the equipment", "bbox": [162.5, 1054.7, 1086.2, 1075.5]}, {"text": "lease financing business. Commercial lease financing receivables represented 11.9% of commercial loans at", "bbox": [162.5, 1079.7, 1064.6, 1100.5]}, {"text": "December 31, 2013, and 13.3% at December 31, 2012.", "bbox": [162.5, 1104.7, 620.5, 1125.5]}, {"text": "Commercial loan modification and restructuring", "bbox": [162.5, 1147.7, 565.8, 1168.6]}, {"text": "We modify and extend certain commercial loans in the normal course of business for our clients. Loan", "bbox": [162.5, 1190.7, 1018.8, 1211.6]}, {"text": "modifications vary and are handled on a case by case basis with strategies responsive to the specific", "bbox": [162.5, 1215.7, 995.9, 1236.6]}, {"text": "circumstances of each loan and borrower. In many cases, borrowers have other resources and can reinforce the", "bbox": [162.5, 1240.7, 1086.2, 1261.6]}, {"text": "credit with additional capital, collateral, guarantees or income sources.", "bbox": [162.5, 1265.7, 752.2, 1286.6]}, {"text": "Modifications are negotiated to achieve mutually agreeable terms that maximize loan credit quality while at the", "bbox": [162.5, 1308.8, 1093.3, 1329.6]}, {"text": "same time meeting our clients’ financing needs. Modifications made to loans of creditworthy borrowers not", "bbox": [162.5, 1333.8, 1061.7, 1354.6]}, {"text": "experiencing financial difficulties and under circumstances where ultimate collection of all principal and interest", "bbox": [162.5, 1358.8, 1103.6, 1379.6]}, {"text": "is not in doubt are not classified as TDRs. In accordance with applicable accounting guidance, a loan is classified", "bbox": [162.5, 1383.8, 1108.2, 1404.6]}, {"text": "as a TDR only when the borrower is experiencing financial difficulties and a creditor concession has been", "bbox": [162.5, 1408.8, 1046.8, 1429.6]}, {"text": "granted.", "bbox": [162.5, 1433.8, 230.2, 1454.6]}, {"text": "60", "bbox": [627.1, 1484.1, 647.9, 1504.9]}]}